        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 11:33AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 1133 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles south of Farmerville, or 13 miles northeast of Ruston, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Downsville, Eureka, Rocky Branch, D Arbonne and Loch Lomon.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
